article.headline: Centenary 86, Oral Roberts 79
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Caleb Green had 23 points and eight rebounds to lead Oral Roberts past Centenary 88-65 in a Mid-Continent Conference game on Saturday night. Green, a 6-foot-7 sophomore, was 8-of-9 from the field. ORU's Ken Tutt scored 21 points as he sank 5-of-7 three-point shots. Larry Owens added 15 points and nine rebounds for the Golden Eagles (12-4, 3-1 Mid-Con) while teammate Mickey Michalec had season-highs of 13 points and 10 rebounds. Chad Maclies paced the Gents (2-13, 0-4) with 20 points and seven rebounds. Tyrone Hamilton added 14 points for Centenary, which has lost seven in a row and is 0-8 away from home. ORU led 32-22 at intermission and Centenary didn't cut its deficit under 10 during the rest of the game. Green opened the second half with a layup and Tutt followed with a trey for a 37-22 advantage. Hamilton then sank a 3-pointer, but a basket by Michalec sparked a 14-2 roll that boosted ORU's advantage to 51-27 with 14:46 left. The Golden Eagles' lead was 60-39 at 11:24 before a Michalec layup and Owens trey ignited a 22-4 run that made it 82-43. Centenary outscored ORU 22-6 during the final six minutes. ORU, which improved to 6-0 at home, outrebounded Centenary 41-31. The Golden Eagles shot 56 percent from the field compared to Centenary's 34 percent. Jonathan Bluitt had 10 assists for ORU. Centenary never led. Green, who began the game with a dunk, had seven points in the first 3:45 to stake ORU to a 9-2 lead. The Golden Eagles' advantage increased to 19-6 with 12:24 left in the half. Maclies scored 14 points in the first 15:45, including a layup that cut the Gents' deficit to 24-18. But Tutt answered with a trey and ORU ended the half with an 8-4 spurt.
